  "original_title": "IMF  \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd\u0da2\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca 24 \u0daf\u0dcf \u0d91\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "IMF representatives are coming on the 24th",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The International Monetary Fund said in a statement that a delegation of the International Monetary Fund will visit Sri Lanka from the 24th to the 31st of August in order to reach staff-level agreements for providing a detailed credit facility to Sri Lanka.",
        "However, the International Monetary Fund says that it expects sufficient guarantees from the creditors during the visit of its representatives to Sri Lanka.",
        "It has been stated that in order to provide the facilities of the financial fund, a certificate obtained from the creditor regarding the debt restructuring in Sri Lanka is required.",
        "The International Monetary Fund also said that economic and financial reforms and policies will be discussed with the Sri Lankan authorities during this visit.",
        "As Sri Lanka's public debt has been assessed as unsustainable, IMF Executive Board approval of the Extended Credit Facility Program requires adequate assurances from Sri Lanka's creditors that debt sustainability will be restored, the IMF said.",
        "The IMF further announced that the IMF staff will work with other stakeholders during the visit and that the team will be led by Mr. Peter Brewer and Mr. Masahiro Nozaki."
      ],
